metadata.name: Wanderer #149
metadata.description:
Wanderer is an algorithm which uses hexagonal Truchet tiles to produce meandering paths of color. Originally created back in February, I am releasing it as part of this week's #fxhashturnsone celebration.

100% of primary sales will go the the Processing foundation.

Thank you to fx(hash) and to the entire generative art community. 

CONTROLS:

1-9: Increase resolution and save image in PNG format

For third party license information, please see license.md

David Brice Allen
November 2022

metadata.name: FHX-1 #52
metadata.description:
#fxhashturnsone 

All primary proceeds are donated to The Processing Foundation and Girls Who Code.
https://processingfoundation.org
https://girlswhocode.com/about-us


Controls:
[s] save as PNG.


Notes:
Artworks take a few seconds to render.

I generated the raw base unprocessed GAN seeds used in this piece offline from various custom styleGAN models. All the mixing and processing steps are done generatively online in p5.js by the FHX algorithm.
